# .envrc — direnv: auto-loads the Nix dev environment when you enter this directory
# Requires: direnv + nix-direnv (configured via home-manager)
#
# Usage: copy this file to a project root, run `direnv allow` once.
# VS Code with the direnv extension picks it up automatically.

# Load the project's flake.nix devShell
use flake

# Optional: load a .env file for secrets (do not commit .env to git)
# dotenv_if_exists .env

# Agent task context — set TASK_ID before launching mb sandboxes
# export TASK_ID="MYPROJ-42"
